The paper discusses the use of automated data-driven decision-making systems, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on fairness and non-discriminative decision-making suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR), as these fields often deal with issues of fairness and privacy. Finally, the use of optimization techniques in the proposed framework suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SI).
